##The chickens, when the plague spread,

Micro-signal GQREPORT

Function introduction, record the rise and fall of the characters and changes in the value of the Times. Complete, true, in-depth, accurate non-fiction stories, sent to you every week.

Xing Haichao, who raised three hundred thousand chickens, felt that the road was closed to the young chicks. What was wrong with this logic: human life is bigger than the sky, but if something goes wrong in the market, it is people's livelihood that is in question. Doesn't this human life also need people's livelihood to be maintained?

···············

❶

"New Year's first shot, four boxes first. "

The pit has been dug 1 meter deep, has been extended more than 10 meters, Henan Luohe Wuyang County, Wucheng's outdoor temperature is less than 8 °C, 36,000 chicken chicks are in the pit bottom "Ji Ji" non-stop, small hairy head lively jostle to and fro. For the previous 21 days, they were still 36,000 breeding eggs, waiting to be hatched in a precision, sanitary and safe incubator at the constant temperature of 37 degrees at Kinji poultry. On January 23, the last month of the lunar calendar, the twenty-nine day old chicks were dumped, one by one, into a newly dug pit.

A few shovels of excavator, the soil covered the chicken chicks. Workers are big men, or can not help but shed tears, "JI JI JI" sound quickly become small, disappear, general manager Zhang Zhengang did not cry, but "the heart like a needle.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, Zhang Zhengang buried the second batch, still 36,000. On the third day, 36,000; on the fifth day, 36,000. There are six more in the pipeline. Not surprisingly, he will lose a total of 360,000 chickens by this time of year in 2020.

Zhang didn't bother to discuss it with his family, as if his mother was in the final stages of cancer, and his 10 year old daughter, who loves chickens, never left the factory. The video of the chickens being buried alive was eventually seen by the family, and the wife said the daughter was crying her eyes out, "daddy is so cruel! "

It wasn't dad. Zhang Zhengang can not explain, in the final analysis, this is "no way to approach. ".

Zhang Zhengang has buried nearly 150,000 chickens alive (photo: Zhang Zhengang) 

From January 20, the new pneumonia epidemic was severe, roads were closed, live poultry markets were closed, feed could not be brought in, chicken seedlings could not be sold, and chicken farmers across the country spent a panic-stricken Spring Festival. Under one of the most severe road closures in the country, the chickens could not even escape from their villages. Carrian Group, a native of Shangqiu, Henan Province, was unable to sell his young chickens and was crushed to death. She threw the dead chickens into the boiler and turned them into ashes. Wang Junjie of Xuchang, Henan Province, pours dozens of fresh-hatched chickens into sacks and sends them to his friends at a dog farm to be boiled, fed to the dogs and confiscated from them. Xing Haichao, from Xingyang, Henan Province, posted a short video of a buried chicken with yellow hair mixed with loess, accompanied by his steady henan-accented voice-over: "first gun of the New Year, dump four boxes first. ". The top-trending comment received 1,170 likes: "Don't you want it? It's all life! "

Liu Hujin from Huainan, Anhui, told us, crying. On January 21, he pulled 9,650 chicken chicks home and saw the news from Wuhan that he didn't take it seriously: the report mentioned only wild animals, not poultry. In the days that followed, the pop-up News on his mobile phone made him nervous: The number of confirmed cases was climbing, people were getting sick and the live poultry market was shut down. On the second day of the New Year, he and his wife calculated that the chickens would cost between $170,000 and $190,000 to raise, and if they didn't sell in two months, it would be $170,000 and $190,000 to put them to bed.

Each additional bag of grain was wasted three hundred more yuan. Liu Hujin cut off the grain for the chicken that day, and the hungry chickens gathered together.

On the third day of the Lunar New Year, Liu hujin carried a shovel. A man dug a big hole in the wasteland outside the village. The hole was three meters wide and four meters long.

On the evening of the fourth day of the Lunar New Year, 9,650 chickens were put into feed bags. Liu Hujin drove the electric car twice, hit the lights and fell down.

❷
"chickens are much more normal than me. "
Messages from the outside passed in layers, to the provinces, to the counties, to the nerve endings of the country. When word reached Wang Ping's chicken shack, it had been nine days since academician Zhong Nanshan had arrived in Wuhan. On the fourth night of the Lunar New Year, Wang Ping from Kaifeng, Henan Province, called her brother-in-law. Could you pick up something for me? Brother-in-law said, your village has been closed road, I can not cross!

Wang Ping ran out of the chicken shack 200 meters away, only to find that the village road has been tightly sealed. She stared at the chicken coop these days, the village has built a mud wall, the village cadres at the intersection, who do not let.

Within a few days, villages large and small had closed their roads, village by village, with telephone poles, excavators, or a car directly in the middle of the road, no one in the car, no key.

Xing Haichao originally intended to send chicken seedlings, New Year's Day, a wake up, his village, like a bunker, is surrounded by large and small piles of earth, every 500 meters there is a traffic police or public security guard. The guard said he could get out with a permit from the village committee. After a day, the village committee's certificate is invalid, the nearest customer in five miles away can not be transported.

Get the deposit a single single back, Xinghai ultra-urgent. A few miles from his house, he managed to get his car onto the highway, checking the exits one by one. Instead of getting better, things got worse. Traffic police stopped him: "is your life big (important) , or your seedlings big (important) ? "

The chicks can't get out. The eggs can't get out. The Liu Weitao of Henan New town looks at an egg one by one to accumulate in the storehouse, anxious even the chicken house all does not want to enter, "does not know when is a head" . In his hands, more than 10,000 breeding chickens still lay eggs every day. Breeding eggs must be sold to the hatchery within 10 days, or they will become fresh eggs. The difference between a fresh egg and a case of breeding eggs is hundreds of yuan. A day's loss will be 2,000 to 3,000 yuan, and a month's loss will be nearly 100,000 yuan. His wife was angry with him when she picked up the egg, but he couldn't help it. He just sat there with his mouth closed.

He heard about Wuhan twenty-eight years ago, but thought, "it's not bird flu, it has nothing to do with chickens, " until the second afternoon of the Lunar New Year, when he walked from the West End of the village to the east end and saw the road blocked and thought, so many medical workers have gone to Wuhan, a few days should do it. A few days later I saw that the mound had been replaced by a red iron tile, which sealed the road so tightly that the egg could not be sent out.

The village blocked the road with Red Metal Shingles (photo: Liu Weitao) 

So did Ms. Wang and her family. No one in the village had ever been to Wuhan, and there were no suspected patients. She saw the news before the Spring Festival, always feel "the country is so strong, can cure it in one fell swoop" , did not prepare more feed. There was nothing to be expected now, they breathed in the flock, and the purveyor of fodder said that it would not come, and that it would die by itself. And they said, what about the loss? The other side still said no matter, and then to say, what other dealers do what we do.

Wang Ping can only reduce the number of feeding 20,000 chickens, the original two times a day, can only feed once. Normally 30 bags, but now 10 isn't enough. Originally this stage, the chicken grew the fastest, hair is less, the flesh on the body is red, now a look on thin. The husband goes in to add material in the evening, a turn on the light, hear the noise of fodder car, the chicken all jumped up at once, "seem to be very hungry very hungry appearance, quite pitiable" .

One day, her husband took out more than 10 dead chickens, they are small and can not compete with others. Wang Ping dug a big hole in the dry ditch and buried them together.

Carrian Group went into the Henhouse and saw that fifty or sixty chickens had been crushed to death. Her family's broiler has grown to sixty days, the third day should be out of the pen. But the animal quarantine can not open out, dare not go out. 40,000 broilers crammed into cages, couldn't sleep at night, and the ones under them died. The dead chickens lay there, their upper feathers gone, their flesh trampled to shreds, and you could see it at a glance.

There's a boiler in the house. Dead chickens go straight to the stove. Chicken seedling home 60 days, day to feed, night to check, afraid of low temperature, afraid of mice hurt it. Now Carrian Group was throwing them into the oven one by one. It was useless to feel sorry for them. She was even more sorry to see her parents wipe away their tears.

Along with the roadblock is a family's cash flow operation. Gao Fei, a local chicken seller in Chongqing, just received a statement last year showing a balance of 2,576.34 yuan. Xiao Ying's family in Yuncheng, Shanxi, borrowed $600,000 last year to repair a chicken coop and buy equipment. The loan has to be paid off once a year, $100,000 at a time. They don't know if they're GONNA make money or lose it, so they gamble. When the time to buy chicken seedlings catch swine fever, pig farmers sad, change to raise chickens, push the price of chicken seedlings rose ship high, to 6. Now they're selling the cheapest chickens, $2.50 each, and no one's pulling them. "I was just about to give the money back when all of a sudden this happened. "

This year happens to be sister Xiu's Year of birth. Her personal signature on wechat reads, "there is no elevator on the road to success, only step by step climbing the ladder. ". But this ladder always breaks. In the first half of this year, she managed to earn five hundred thousand grand from raising chickens, and bought her family a $100,000 Buick Lexus SUV, so she didn't have to drive the van. "World Retribution, earned to return" , the last three months market is not good, she has lost four hundred thousand, Spring Festival again encounter epidemic, soon to level off.

Zhang Houfeng, of Huainan, Anhui Province, has only two or three days left. He used the "eastern hope" feed, these days call every day, the factory told him that there is no raw materials, a little stock is gone. He also saw wholesalers in his circle of friends saying that the market was not allowed to sell, that the stalls of the big distributors had been dismantled and that no one dared to pull the chickens. "the ones with the chickens in their hands were all finished. ".

On New Year's Eve, Zhang Houfeng did not even give the child the lucky money. During the day, he picked up the spirit to the henhouse inspection, 30,000 Ma chicken spirit erect, do not know that he will face the dilemma of starvation, but he was depressed, "chicken than I am much more normal. "

❸

"It doesn't matter if the mayor is your brother. "

In order to keep 20,000 chickens alive for one more day, Wang Ping's husband rode his electric bicycle out early in the morning. He would go to the commissary to harvest the corn, and then find a place to break the seeds. Roads are blocked in villages, cars can not get through them, and electric bikes can be hauled over mounds of dirt and telephone poles. He could only carry a little at a time, four or five trips back and forth, barely enough for a day.

On the fifth day, the Sichuan Deyang show sister finally contact a customer, willing to tow away 25,000 chicken seedlings. The next day, she loaded up 5,000 of the chicks and took them to the local livestock bureau. According to the process, the animal husbandry bureau to chicken photography, spot-check, disinfection, she then reported the buyer's identity card information and telephone number, you can get approval procedures.

But on this day, the staff let her prove that these chickens are really from her factory. The staff asked: The village is closed road, how do I know where your chicken came from? Xiu Jie answered, the village indeed closed the road, a two-way Lane, block a car on the left, but also left a hole on the right, in case of emergency. The answer was not accepted and she had to go back to the village to prove it. Back at the Animal Husbandry Bureau, the staff added that the buyer also had to get approval from the local animal husbandry bureau. So she returned to the village, in the village to pick up the customer, repeated to the buyer's side of the Animal Husbandry Bureau call.

On the phone, the two sides of the staff communication. Can Hang up the phone, the local staff said to Xiu Jie, the other party is using a cell phone, must use 028 landline to call us before we recognize. Their words sound reasonable: This is a special time, you have to understand.

"I a chicken five cents to lose money to deal with, I understand you, who will understand me? " Show sister and pulled 5000 chicken seedlings home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Chicken seedlings of Xiu Jie in Deyang, Sichuan Province (photo: Xiu Jie)

In the face of the epidemic, it doesn't matter that the village chief is his brother. Xinghaichao to find when the village chief's brother, brother told him, oneself also can not open road, Xinghaichao to find animal husbandry bureau, the bureau answered: Human Life is greater than days, you that loss in front of human life, nothing. He understood this truth, but also felt that the logic seems not quite right: human life is bigger than the day, but the market is out of order, that is people's livelihood is out of order, this life does not also need people's livelihood to maintain it?

Over the phone, Xing read a notice in a thick Henan accent, issued on Jan. 30 by the General Office of the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, the General Office of the Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China, and the General Office of the Ministry of Public Security, he plans to unite with other local chicken farmers to "strictly prohibit unauthorized blocking of roads and roads, and to maintain the normal circulation of 'vegetable baskets' products and agricultural Means of production. " Call the mayor's hotline together.

A letter of application is circulating in several Shandong farmers'wechat groups: to the esteemed Shen County agricultural and rural bureau, the leaders of the Animal Husbandry Service Center... ? . The letter asked three main questions: What should we do about the farmers'financial ruin this time? What about the large number of dead poultry? Could there be an animal plague superimposed? When the epidemic is over, what will everyone eat. ? Signed by the applicant who wrote: LIVESTOCK AND POULTRY PRODUCERS! At the end there is a sentence: please the majority of livestock and POULTRY FARMERS SPREAD FORWARD!

A chicken farmer forwarded the letter to a chicken technical teaching group. Five people followed with likes. The group leader quickly replied: There is no leader in this group, you can not see the leader.

Xiao Ying, 23, couldn't figure out how to help her chicken parents get through the ordeal? She works as a graphic artist at a Taobao shop in Hangzhou and returns to her home in Yuncheng, Shanxi Province, for Chinese New Year. She didn't know how to raise chickens, so she looked it up on the Internet. She is in Douyin search"collect chicken", contacted a circle, nobody collects, also do not know when will collect. The 5th night, she did not sleep all night, suddenly thought, the attention of the network is highest fastest, perhaps can help appeal. She logged on to Li Jiaqi, Maomaojie, and more than 60 other internet celebrities'home pages and live rooms, sending them private messages and comments asking them to help the chicken farmers. twenty-four hours passed without a response.

She dare not bring up these voluntarily at home, answer an interview telephone to also want to stand in the hill outside chicken coop inside. Without a computer at home, parents' knowledge of the Internet is limited to Wechat and Douyin on their mobile phones. "You (to interview) don't make sense to them. They don't understand the concept of magazines and business numbers. "

Yi Zhonghua, 43, is more aggressive in his approach to the media. He added a group of 11 farmers, where someone posted a Qr Code on the State Council's epidemic monitoring platform, indicating that they were soliciting information on epidemic prevention and control. He scanned the code and filled in his information carefully, hoping someone would help. He also left a message under the headline all livestock breeders retweet, and then received calls from four media outlets.

Yi Zhonghua pulled two reporters into a wechat group of farmers, want to help reporters understand more about the situation. But after the reporter into the group to introduce themselves, the group soon emerged against the voice, several farmers asked reporters must put the identity card photo issued in the group, self-identification.

Some farmers directly blame Yi in the group:

"You don't get to know people like that. "

"Do you know each other? Or are you related? "

"You can't say anything about that. "

"What if it's a spy? "

.....

Finally someone directly threatened Yi Zhonghua: You come out to speak, or immediately report to the police!

Reporters backed away from the group, Yi Zhonghua felt the reaction in the group he also understood, this group of farmers too far from the media, "do a bad thing easy, you want to help, they absolutely do not believe. "

❹

"What can I do, what can I do? "

Yi's chicken coop in Yichang, Hubei Province, was converted from a pig sty. In 2019, he and his wife spent 10 days adding a ceiling over the pigsty, with Straw curtains, mats, insulation cotton and insulation, and buying an online coal-fired stove instead of a small stove to heat the seedlings.

The year before last, Yi Zhonghua was still a pig farmer. In June, he heard through his wechat group of pig farmers that African swine fever was coming. The 10 sows and 60 porkers in the pen were sold on the scale at 300 yuan a sow and 6 yuan a catty before swine fever reached Yichang. According to Yi Zhonghua, in June 2019, swine fever spread to Yichang city, and those who were not well informed were driven to their homes to be electrocuted and buried. The loss was much worse than his.

Yi Zhonghua's chicken coop transformed from a pig sty in Yichang, Hubei Province (photo: Yi Zhonghua)

It was a few pig wechat group saved Yi Zhonghua, this year he held the hands of 11 chicken groups, but a little gossip did not get. A few days before the Spring Festival, Yi Zhonghua saw a retweet on wechat group. By the time new pneumonia could have affected the livestock industry, it was too late and the order to close the live poultry market had already come down. 5,000 adult chickens will be ready for sale on New Year's Eve, and no one will dare to come to the market or shop where they are normally sold. Twenty days earlier, he had picked up 6,000 chicks from the hatchery and placed them in a greenhouse he had built.

Big Entrepreneur Zhang Zhengang also did not escape. He is always ahead of the news. He is always ahead of the news. More than 20 years ago, he was popularised in Shenzhen, "environmental" concept, after returning to the location of the chicken farm is different from others, a few years ago set off the ban on environmental protection tide, also did not affect his head. Half a month before the 2017 H7N9 bird flu pandemic, he had also detected "something is wrong" ahead of time, slaughtering tens of thousands of large chickens, and escaped with a loss of one million.

This time, he didn't hit it at all. No one had expected that a pneumonia in another province would affect their own batch of eggs, chicken seedlings and live without disease and disaster on the big chicken. Zhang predicted that if the blockade continued for another three months, three million million yuan would be lost. Fortunately, compared with the private chicken farmers, he has strong economic strength, at the moment can still hold.

Ordinary small-scale retail is the end of the end of the information. The Xiaoying family learned of the road closure three or four days before the Lunar New Year from Douyin. Chicken prices hit rock bottom in a day, and there were fewer carts to haul the goods. My parents finally got in touch with one of them, and they said they'd be here. The chicken was 118 days old, with two days to go. I got a call at noon. $2.50. Mother said, no can sell it, anyway to pay, then less compensation. Father was reluctant to give it a second thought.

Call back in half an hour, and they say, "No more. ".

The decision to raise chickens came in early 2019, when a family borrowed $600,000 to start raising chickens. Xiaoying's Huzhang village is two hours'drive from the city. The village is a wasteland where no crops can be grown. The villagers can only go out to work, doing odd jobs and part-time jobs. Parents also work in Guangzhou for many years, old, waist is not good, the salary can not afford Xiaoying and younger brother. My parents were thinking of doing something else.

Xiaoying's mother saw her friend raise chickens and made 60,000 yuan in one batch. They didn't know other industries or people, so they decided to raise chickens too. The family deposits only 20,000 to 30,000, can not find a bank loan, to find the interests of private lending higher than bank interest, the annual demand for 100,000. They bought a mountain-side wasteland in the village, set up a site, bought fully automated equipment, registered for a license plate, and were ready to gamble. The family also thought, bird flu just over two years, it should not come out so soon.

But now, the live poultry market closed, no one to collect chickens, feed can not be shipped in, the Xiaoying family's feed can last up to three days. Ying doesn't dare to bring it up at home. Whenever she does, her parents cry. Two parents sit at home every night crying, saying that natural disasters can not.

After the African swine fever, Yi Zhonghua family no savings, junior high school education Yi Zhonghua search on Baidu, self-taught to build greenhouses and chicken procedures. He borrowed 40,000 or 50,000 yuan from friends and relatives, and put it all in.

After four months of feeding 5,000 adult chickens with nowhere to sell, Yi Zhonghua now owes 150,000 yuan to the feed mill, with interest still rolling. He planned to go out to work, but he felt that a person from Hubei would be discriminated against if he went out. He might have to go back to just growing oranges to live on, he estimated, the hands of the family to pay the debt for three to five years, "No way, how to what way? "

Now, those 11 wechat groups, every day in the spread of similar buried chicken video. Yi Zhonghua had planned that when his 11-year-old daughter went to school and the feed was completely eaten up, he would dig a three-meter pit in the area where today's free-range chickens are kept. Ten square meters would be enough, and all the thousands of chickens would be dealt with.

❺

Waiting for the good news

An application letter to the bureau of Animal Husbandry, still circulating on Wechat in different provinces, was always addressed to: Livestock and poultry producers. The date was changed from January 30th to January 31st.

Li Tao in Kaifeng, Henan Province, has more than 10,000 meat chickens he could not transport, which were released 20 days ago. He survived bird flu, buried chickens, and finally got a government subsidy, which wasn't much to lose. Now he has to look forward to the possibility of a second subsidy.

Liu Yusheng of Tai'an, Shandong Province, thinks subsidies are better than nothing. He said business losses and profits, if the loss, "the responsibility of the big head is still in their own body, that you practice in this industry is not enough. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhang Zhengang and his chicken farm (photo: Zhang Zhengang)

Zhang Zhengang failed to become the first to escape the crisis, this time, he became the local first batch of chickens buried alive chicken farmers. "The long pain is better than the short-term pain, " he knew not to bury hard-hearted, raised to sell, losses will only be more than now. His mobile phone installed a lot of news clients, from the local Dahe Network to the people's net, Xinhua, "only the official things I believe. ".

On the fifth day of the first lunar month, Zhang Zhengang contacted the local Red Cross Society, and then contacted the Hubei Branch, intending to sell the eggs to Wuhan. He's got it all figured out. A cart, five tons of eggs. The other side thanked him for his kindness, said, we are short of medical supplies, other temporarily do not receive, wait for later need, will call you back. Zhang Zhengang waiting for this call back every day, as if only to donate these eggs, his heart will be a bit more stable.

But now, all we can do is wait, wait for the village to close, wait for slaughterhouses, feed mills to go to work, wait for the live poultry market to open, wait for the epidemic to pass.

Zhang Zhengang sits on his chicken farm, his hands 70,000 breeding chickens, every day in spite of laying eggs.
